    "4 and we evaluated the displayed graphs based on the following criteria: Prompt 6 led to an answer with a hierarchical graph representation of the important classes defined in the DBpedia ontology.",
    "The diagram already met our requirements regarding the minimum number and labelling after the first answer and can be seen in the Supplemental Online Resources.The class hierarchy was represented by the rdfs:subPropertyOf relation, and the nodes were labelled in prefix notation, as were the edges.",
